{"title_page": "Prabhat Roy", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Prabhat Roy\n| birth_date         = \n| nationality        = [[India]]n\n| occupation         = [[Film maker]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/cosmic-sex-was-refused-screening-at-nandan-for-aesthetic-reasons-says-director-prabhat-roy/articleshow/52894788.cms|title='Cosmic Sex' was refused screening at Nandan for aesthetic reasons, says director Prabhat Roy|website=The Times of India|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n| notable_works      = {{ubl|''Shwet Paatharer Thala''|''Sandhyatara''|''[[Lathi (1996 film)|Lathi]]''}}\n| awards             = {{ubl|[[National Film Award for Best Film on Family Welfare|National Award]]|BFJA Award}}\n}}\n\n'''Prabhat Roy''' ({{lang-bn|\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09ad\u09be\u09a4 \u09b0\u09be\u09af\u09bc}}; born in Jamshedpore, in 1946) is a former [[India]]n director.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/people/prabhat-roy-80775|title=Prabhat Roy movies, filmography, biography and songs - Cinestaan.com|website=Cinestaan|access-date=2019-08-14}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite web\n|url=http://photogallery.indiatimes.com/articleshow/2344727.cms\n|title=Prabhat Roy  - Calcutta - Events - Society - Indiatimes Photogallery\n|publisher=indiatimes.com\n|accessdate=2008-11-14\n|last=\n|first=\n}}\n</ref>\nHe received several awards including two [[National Film Award for Best Film on Family Welfare|National Awards]].\n\nHis first directorial venture was ''Pratidan'' (1983).<ref>\n{{cite web\n |url        = http://www.seventymm.com/Actor/7916/Prabhat_Roy\n |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080307015847/http://www.seventymm.com/Actor/7916/Prabhat_roy\n |url-status   = dead\n |archive-date = 2008-03-07\n |title      = Prabhat Roy\n |publisher  = www.seventymm.com\n |accessdate = 2008-11-14\n}}\n</ref>\